review_blob: Not much more to say than what everyone else has said.  This is my favorite beer much less my favorite IPA.

review_blob: This is an amazing IPA for those whove tried everything else.  Great balance, perfect carbonation and full of great hop flavor.
beer_name: Avery The Maharaja Imperial India Pale Ale

review_blob: Another one of my first "real" beers.  I prefer this as a session beer on a hot summer day with some good Mexican food.  Nothing more, nothing less.

I have to give props to my first "real" beer.  I wish I could be more subjective and give it more points but there are much better, newer draught beers that make it tough.  Nonetheless, an all-time, sentimental favorite.
This is about as good an IPA as it gets.  I go between this and Sculpin from Ballast Point.  If youre a hop head like me, you will be sure to enjoy the DH 90.
Simply amazing.  Just the right amount of chocolate and hops.  This is the chocolate mole of beers.
Very solid ale.  Nice malt and clean finish.  Great after work beer.  Pairs well with good smoked cheese.
Not a big fan of "flavored" beers but this one is very smooth and balanced.  Great session beer.
beer_name: Ballast Point Abandon Ship Smoked Lager - Chipotle
